comments: If you\'re interested in seriously pursuing French I\'d recommend her. She\'s tough but fair, and pretty nice. She lived in France for 7 years and is a translator so she knows her stuff.

Great Prof! She does one Le\xc3\xa7on a week and if you have the MTWTF class, you often get F off. She assigns online HW each week, but it helps A TON for the tests. If you forget a week, she gives one HW amnesty day. She is really nice and very helpful! She is a VCU alum. and studied/worked in France for 10 years! She know her stuff! Prof. Gore rocks!

I really liked her. she really wants to help you and for you to get good grades. she gave us a lot of extra credit. her tests are hard and there a lot of homework which is easy just annoying and quite cumbersome. she lived in france for 8 years so she knows a lot. she is willing to listen to any ideas that you may have to make her teaching better.
She kicked my ass and then handed it to me.... I LEARNED ALOT....
She seems completely unprepared for each class, making it hard to pay attention or care what she\'s saying. She\'s a horrible professor and should be avoided. That being said, she is a nice lady
Awful teacher. If you want to pass don\'t take her. Prepare to have tons of h.w. and her test are hard.
